# React Native Reusables (UI)

When implementing or changing **user-facing UI** in this Expo app, use **[React Native Reusables](https://reactnativereusables.com/)** as the component source of truth.

## Requirements

- Prefer existing project primitives under [`src/components/ui/`](src/components/ui/) (Button, Text, Icon, etc.) and patterns that already match the Reusables setup.
- For **new** controls (dialogs, sheets, forms, lists, etc.), follow the docs at [reactnativereusables.com](https://reactnativereusables.com/) and align with the same stack (e.g. NativeWind, `@rn-primitives/*` where the project uses them) instead of ad-hoc one-off components.
- Do **not** introduce a second design system (random third-party component kits, raw RN widgets where a Reusable exists) unless the user explicitly asks for an exception.
- If a Reusable pattern is missing for a screen, **compose** from existing `ui` primitives before adding unrelated dependencies.

## Non-goals

- This rule does **not** override backend-only work (Supabase SQL, Edge functions with no UI).
- Domain copy and navigation structure still follow `CONTEXT.md`, PRD, and Expo Router skills; this rule only governs **how** UI is built.
